    "daily_lesson": {
      "term": "Cash Drag",
      "explanation_en": "Cash drag occurs when a portfolio holds too much uninvested cash, causing it to underperform when markets rise \u2014 because cash earns nothing while stocks gain. Today is a perfect example: we have 4 open slots but only $180 in cash, so we can't capitalize on a strong risk-on day. Managing cash levels is a key part of portfolio construction.",
